### Variaveis
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
@authEmail = "admin@example.com"
@authPassword = "password123"

### 1. Health & DB
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
---
GET {{baseUrl}}/db/ping

### 2. Signup
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": {{authEmail}},
  "password": {{authPassword}},
  "tenantName": "Example Corp"
}

### 3. Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": {{authEmail}},
  "password": {{authPassword}}
}

### 4. Fetch User Session (Me)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
# The token is sent automatically if your HTTP client saves cookies

### 5. List Tenants
GET {{baseUrl}}/tenants

### 6. Create another Tenant
POST {{baseUrl}}/tenants
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Second Tenant"
}

### 7. Select Tenant (switch context)
# Change the tenantId below to a valid one returned by GET /tenants
POST {{baseUrl}}/tenants/select
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tenantId": "REPLACE_WITH_VALID_UUID"
}

### 8. Scope Check (must happen after successful login/select)
GET {{baseUrl}}/tenant/scope-check

### 9. Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
